class=title>   Hmm...Raid Rules that are Fair?</span><hr size=1> Not really possible, unless you break down what you want to be fair to.  Justise had the right idea in asking if we wanted to be fair to the &quot;guild&quot; or to the &quot;individual&quot; but it is really deeper than that.  Its a matter of priorities.  What's more important to the people on the server?<br>
<br>
Having at least one shot each at killing VS?  Well that needs a specific solution.<br>
<br>
Being able to lead a raid against VS?  Again a specific solution.<br>
<br>
Being free to do what you can do given the number of friends (guildmates) you have?  Also a different solution.<br>
<br>
What's interesting about the above examples (and I have more and you probably do to) is that the solution to each is very easy to achieve, but that solution conflicts directly with the others.  <br>
<br>
I can give you a plan that will allow each person on the server that wants to kill VS a shot at it in a fair manner.  That's easy, the problem is that the solution conflicts with what other people want to do.  They may want to lead a raid and invite their friends only.  They may want the freedom to preform their raid the way they want to.<br>
<br>
The question is not what should the solution be.  The question is &quot;What is the problem with the current system?&quot;  Everyone has their own ideas.  Everyone sees their own problems.  Independants, small guilds and large guilds have their own priorities.  Make a list of the problems and work on a solution.  The solution WILL require that sacrifices be made.  Adune's system has some great points, and it could solve the problems, but the reason why it won't be implemented is because some people/guilds aren't willing to make the sacrifices needed to make it work.<br>
<br>
The fact is that without a specific listing of the problems seen in the current system, and a little willingness on the part of everyone to sacrifice a little, there will be no solution...ever.  It won't happen.  There are too many people with their own priorities.  There are too many people that need things to be their way or no way.  Too few people are willing to give a little for the sake of the server.<br>
<br>
My2cp.<br>
<br>
[NOTE:  I did not include specific solutions to problems, because frankly, I don't understand what the actual problem is.  One person says the problem is that they never get to go, and another says the problem is that so and so gets to go too much.  If I understood the real problem, I'd offer some suggestions.] <p>Peace,<BR>
